<b><i><center><FONT FACE="arial" size="5"color="white">Subject: </font><FONT FACE="arial" size="5"color="red">Diplomacy Mission</font></center></i></b><p><p>
<center><FONT FACE="arial" size="3"color="white"><b>| <a href="#view">View Comments</a> | <a href="#add">Add Your Comments</a> | </b></font></center><p><center><img src="/images/a3.gif"></center><p>
<b><FONT FACE="arial" color="orange">Posted By <a href="mailto:Blizzardeus@aol.com">Blizzardeus Stormrayge (Blizzardeus@aol.com)</a> On 12/04/01:</font></b><br>
Some of our allies have been inviting us on raids and rallys with them, but when the day rolls around, no Brimstoners are there to dispense some indiscriminate justice on the mobs alongside our brothers and sisters in arms.Since the patch/launch process began, I went to RallosZek.net and looked at some other guilds webpages.  Datal is pretty good about listing the true status of guilds, whether they be Random PK, Anti, Neutral, or Roleplay.  A lot of the good guilds out there are unsure of us... that hurts your chances for joining a pick-up group or mini raid.<p>With that said, I have only one suggestion:  See a member of a known anti/neutral guild (even RP guild) that needs a heal?  Give them one.  They need a SoW?  Why the fizuck not?  Newbie char struggling and swarmed with beetles or spiderlings?  Root or snare some.<p>These are all Standard Ops when you see a member of Brimstone, why not extend some courtesy to people that can help us complete those epics and kill dragons later on?  That newbie you help tomorrow could be the alt of some level 60 Cleric that can rezz your decaying ass after you just bought it.  Believe it or not, but that Warrior you heal and buff up could hand you some outstanding piece of equipment that he can't use.<p>Bottom line is, there are plenty of assholes on our server that demand buffs/ports/rezzes ... and then there are those rare few that are generous souls who appreciate what you do for them.

